Prerequisites


Microsoft 365 account with Power Automate license

Access to SharePoint Online

Excel file with minimum wage data

Appropriate permissions to create and manage flows


Step-by-Step Installation

1. Prepare the Excel File


Create or locate your minimum wage tracking Excel file

Ensure it contains a table with these columns:

Jurisdiction (Text)

Effective Date (Date format)



Upload the file to a SharePoint document library

Note the SharePoint site URL and file location


2. Import the Flow


Go to Power Automate

Navigate to My flows

Click Import → Import Package (Legacy)

Select the flow package file from this repository

Click Upload


3. Configure Connections

During import, you'll need to configure these connections:


Excel Online (Business)


Click Select during import

Choose an existing connection or create a new one

Sign in with your Microsoft 365 account if prompted


Office 365 Outlook


Click Select during import

Choose an existing connection or create a new one

Sign in with your Microsoft 365 account if prompted


4. Complete the Import


Review the import setup

Click Import

Wait for the import to complete


5. Configure Flow Settings


Open the imported flow

Click Edit


Update Excel Data Source


Find the List rows present in a table action

Click to edit the action

Configure:

Location: Select your SharePoint site

Document Library: Choose the library containing your Excel file

File: Select your Excel file

Table: Choose the table with minimum wage data




Update Email Recipients


Find the Send an email (V2) action

Update:

To: Enter recipient email address(es)

Cc: Enter CC email address(es) (optional)



Customize the email body if needed


Adjust Schedule (Optional)


Click on the Recurrence trigger

Modify as needed:

Interval: Keep as 1

Frequency: Keep as Day

Time Zone: Change if not using India Standard Time

At these hours: Change from 10 if different time needed




6. Test the Flow


Click Test in the top right

Select Manually

Click Test

Add a test record with Effective Date = Today + 7 days

Verify email is received


7. Enable the Flow


Click Turn on to activate the flow

The flow will now run daily at the scheduled time


Verification Checklist


 Flow imported successfully

 Excel connection configured

 Outlook connection configured

 SharePoint file location updated

 Email recipients updated

 Schedule configured correctly

 Test run completed successfully

 Flow is turned on


Post-Installation


Monitor the flow run history for the first few days

Ensure emails are being sent as expected

Verify date calculations are correct

Document any customizations made


Rollback

If you need to remove the flow:



Go to My flows

Find the "Min wage Report" flow

Click ... (More options)

Select Delete

Confirm deletion
